item.description: Article: https://thedailyadda.com/2026/02/03/doj-takes-down-thousands-of-epstein-documents-to-protect-trump/ I still can't get over how the Republican party approved the nomination of Pam Bondi to lead the DOJ, also with Todd Blanche as Deputy AG. Two of Trump's personal lawyers. And they've done what we've expected--operate like Trump's personal lawyers, while running the DOJ into the ground. Look at that face. What's she thinking? "What a mistake I made taking this job." Or, "I know you're a pedo and you've raped young girls, but despite my hating you, I'm still going to protect you." Well, the DOJ is so screwed up, they couldn't even manage their coverup properly. More Epstein files were released, because of the incessant pressure on the DOJ missing a LEGAL DEADLINE of a full release back in late December. And well... they let slip a lot of unredacted appearances of Trump's name. Trump sees the social media firestorm about his presence in the files, and his behavior... and so he commands Bondi to pull them. Think of it. They tasked THOUSANDS of FBI agents to comb through the Epstein files and redact mention of Trump as well as victims... and they took nearly a whole year and they still didn't get everything. Trump's name appears in them far more than "Harry Potter" appears in all 7 Harry Potter books. And the latest release included images and names of victims.

item.title: We need more Antonio Gramsci here
item.description: Antonio Gramsci called Cultural Hegemony the idea that those in power shape the dominant worldview so deeply that even the oppressed adopt it as “common sense.” People started believing that billionaire success is tied to morality, hard work, or divine favor when in reality, it’s a system built to protect their wealth and status. Cultural hegemony works when the status quo becomes so normalized that challenging it feels irrational. So instead of questioning billionaires or unjust systems, people turn on their neighbors, other tribes, races, unions, grassroots movements, genders; against everything what is not like them but doesn't question the system at all.
